## Schema

### Required

- `bucket_name` (String) Name of the bucket
- `object_key` (String) Object key (path within the bucket)
- `service_name` (String) Service name of the resource representing the id of the cloud project

### Optional

- `legal_hold` (Attributes) Legal hold configuration to apply (see [below for nested schema](#nestedatt--legal_hold))
- `retention` (Attributes) Retention (object lock) configuration to apply (see [below for nested schema](#nestedatt--retention))
- `version_id` (String) Version identifier of the object. When set, the resource manages the lock on that specific version.

### Read-Only

- `id` (String) Resource identifier formatted as `<service_name>/<bucket_name>/<url-encoded object_key>` or `<service_name>/<bucket_name>/<url-encoded object_key>/<version_id>` when a version is targeted.

<a id="nestedatt--retention"></a>

### Nested Schema for `retention`

Required:

- `mode` (String) Retention mode. One of `COMPLIANCE` or `GOVERNANCE`. The third enum value `NONE` is rejected by the API with HTTP 400.
- `retain_until_date` (String) RFC 3339 date/time until which the object is retained.

<a id="nestedatt--legal_hold"></a>

### Nested Schema for `legal_hold`

Required:

- `status` (String) Legal hold status. One of `ON` or `OFF`.

## Import

Because object keys can contain `/`, the object key inside the import ID must be URL-encoded (the same scheme used when the resource is created).

```bash
# object (no version)
terraform import ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_object_lock.example '<service_name>/<bucket_name>/<url-encoded object_key>'

# specific version
terraform import ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_object_lock.example '<service_name>/<bucket_name>/<url-encoded object_key>/<version_id>'
```
